**Framework & Syntax:**
- **Framework:** Vue 3 with Composition API  
- **Syntax:** Uses `<script setup>` syntax

**UI Library:**
- NuxtUI & NuxtUI Pro (our customization of it in our `packages/ui` package)
- Check existing components for examples of @nuxt/ui usage

**Reference Guidelines:**
- Always reference other UI (components/pages/etc.) to ensure consistency in style and values across the project.

**Project/Repository Specifics:**
- **Tailwind Config Settings:**  
  Find these in the `apps/<app>/tailwind.config.ts` file.
- **Design Kit Values:**  
  We generally follow Github Primer design guidelines for values (e.g., spacing numbers, margins, columns, etc.).

**Code Style & Rules:**
- Everything must be mobile responsive and darkmode compatible.
- Use Tailwind classes over custom CSS.
- Use NuxtUI & NuxtUI Pro components.
  
**Additional Reference:**
- Look at existing components in the same app for pattern matching and consistency.
